Learn Eclipse By running digit recognition problem
--------------------------------------------------
1. Set up Eclipse for MNIST
    > eclipse
    In Workspace, write "/home/xxxx/work" where xxxx is the user name 
    (vincent/weilin),
    click Launch
    click "workbench"
    In "Project Explore", there should be a project/directory "keras"
    find "keras/examples/mnist_cnn.py", double click, the Python file will
    show up.
    1) click "Run"
    2) Setup "breakpoint" and "Debug" to step thru the program

2. Tutorial on sklearn - traditional Machine Learning package
   > git clone git://github.com/jakevdp/sklearn_tutorial.git
   > Go over 02.1, 02.2

